'''Kuwado Shrine (鍬戸神社)''' is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|12=draft}} located in Nagabuse (長伏), {{ill|Mishima City|ja|三島市|12=draft}}, {{ill|Shizuoka Prefecture|ja|静岡県|12=draft}}.<ref>[http://www.shizuoka-jinjacho.or.jp/shokai/jinja.php?id=4402053 鍬戸神社] - 静岡県神社庁</ref>

== Overview ==
It is located in the southwestern part of {{ill|Mishima City|ja|三島市|12=draft}}, at the northern end of the Nagabuse district, on the east bank of the Sakai River, adjacent (to the south) to the Matsumoto district's {{ill|Takahashi Shrine (Mishima City)|ja|高橋神社 (三島市)|lt=Takahashi Shrine|lt_ja=高橋神社|12=draft}}.

Its foundation is unknown, but it is identified with the '''{{ill|Shitori Jinja|ja|倭文神社|12=draft}}''' (しとりじんじゃ), a designated {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|12=draft}}, and is recorded in the '{{ill|Izu Kokushinkaichō|ja|伊豆国神階帳|12=draft}}' as "Jūshi'i-jō Kuwado no Myōjin."<ref name="gen">[https://genbu.net/data/izu/kuwato_title.htm 鍬戸神社] - 玄松子</ref><ref name="engi">[http://engishiki.org/izu/bun/iz140204-02.html 鍬戸神社] - 延喜式神社の調査</ref>

In {{ill|Meiji era|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|12=draft}} 6 ({{ill|1873|ja|1873年|12=draft}}), it was Ranked as a {{ill|village shrine|ja|村社|12=draft}}.<ref name="engi"/>

== Deities ==
* {{ill|Shitori no Kami|ja|倭文神|1=Takehazuchi|2=ja|3=天羽槌雄神|4=zh|5=天羽槌雄神|6=fr|7=Takehazuchi|lt=Takehazuchi|lt=Takehazuchi-no-Mikoto|simple|Takehazuchi|fr|Takehazuchi|lt=Takehazuchi|lt=Shizuri-no-Kami|12=draft}} (or unknown)

