'''Kuwado Shrine (鍬戸神社)''' is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located in Nagabuse (長伏), [[:en:Mishima, Shizuoka|Mishima City]], [[:en:Shizuoka Prefecture|Shizuoka Prefecture]].<ref>[http://www.shizuoka-jinjacho.or.jp/shokai/jinja.php?id=4402053 鍬戸神社] - 静岡県神社庁</ref>
== Overview == It is located in the southwestern part of [[:en:Mishima, Shizuoka|Mishima City]], at the northern end of the Nagabuse district, on the east bank of the Sakai River, adjacent (to the south) to the Matsumoto district's {{ill|Takahashi Shrine (Mishima City)|ja|高橋神社 (三島市)|lt=Takahashi Shrine|lt_ja=高橋神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takahashi Shrine (Mishima City)|qq=}}.
Its foundation is unknown, but it is identified with the '''{{ill|Shitori Jinja|ja|倭文神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shitori Jinja|qq=}}''' (しとりじんじゃ), a designated {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|lt=Shikinaisha}}, and is recorded in the '{{ill|Izu Kokushinkaichō|ja|伊豆国神階帳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Izu Kokushinkaichō|qq=}}' as "Jūshi'i-jō Kuwado no Myōjin."<ref name="gen">[https://genbu.net/data/izu/kuwato_title.htm 鍬戸神社] - 玄松子</ref><ref name="engi">[http://engishiki.org/izu/bun/iz140204-02.html 鍬戸神社] - 延喜式神社の調査</ref>
In [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 6 ([[:en:1873|1873]]), it was Ranked as a {{ill|village shrine|ja|村社|lt=Son-sha|1=Modern_system_of_ranked_Shinto_shrines#Village_shrines|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/village shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 近代社格制度}}.<ref name="engi"/>
== Deities == * {{ill|Shitori no Kami|ja|倭文神|1=Takehazuchi|2=ja|3=天羽槌雄神|4=zh|5=天羽槌雄神|6=fr|7=Takehazuchi|lt=Takehazuchi|lt=Takehazuchi-no-Mikoto|simple|Takehazuchi|fr|Takehazuchi|lt=Takehazuchi|lt=Shizuri-no-Kami|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shitori no Kami|13=User:Immanuelle/Takehazuchi|qq=}} (or unknown)
